wiki.summary: Friendly Fire is a song by American rock band Linkin Park, and is the lead single for their compilation album Papercuts. Friendly Fire was a previously unreleased track by the band, and was both written and recorded during the sessions for their seventh studio album One More Light. It is one of the last songs to be recorded with late frontman Chester Bennington before his passing in July 2017, and is one of two songs from the Papercuts tracklist to never be released on streaming platforms, the other being QWERTY. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: Friendly Fire is a song by American rock band Linkin Park, and is the lead single for their compilation album Papercuts. Friendly Fire was a previously unreleased track by the band, and was both written and recorded during the sessions for their seventh studio album One More Light. It is one of the last songs to be recorded with late frontman Chester Bennington before his passing in July 2017, and is one of two songs from the Papercuts tracklist to never be released on streaming platforms, the other being QWERTY. Friendly Fire is also one of four tracks to be penned with Jon Green of English band The Bonfires, with the other three being Battle Symphony, Nobody Can Save Me, and Tidal Wave, another unreleased track. The other two writers of Friendly Fire are second vocalist Mike Shinoda and guitarist Brad Delson. Read more on Last.fm.
